    Normandy Isle and Shores

    Normandy Isle and Shores lies just west of Miami Beach Island and comprises of several small neighborhoods that are made up of single-family homes that surround the picturesque Normandy Shores and Golf Course. The landmass at Normandy Isle and Shores has a canal that runs straight through the center which makes it easier for residents to navigate around the island while offering potential buyers with more opportunities for waterfront homes.

    The average house price at Normandy Isle and Shores ranges from $509,900 to $6,590,000 and features all the bells and whistles one would expect when it comes to luxury living. Normandy Isle and Shores is an exclusive gated-community that offers residents so much more than just amazing waterfront views. Residents also get to have waterfront tennis courts, basketball courts, and many parks and playgrounds along with a community center and a club house.

    Another advantage of living at Normandy Isle and Shores is that you get to live in close proximity to Miami Beach, which is famous for its art deco scene along with many options when it comes to shops and restaurants. It’s easy to see why residential real estate at Normandy Isle and Shores is highly desirable whether the home is facing the waterfront or golf course. Because of its luxury living standards, Normandy Isle and Shores has attracted high net worth individuals such as Frank Sinatra who also owned a home in this exclusive neighborhood.
